 That install applies to "Oscar"  1993 Flair Software. Supported are two
 different floppy AGA versions, the floppy ECS version, the CD남 version and the CD남 Oscar/Diggers-Bundle.

 That install requires WHDLoad to be in the path. It can be found in the
 WHDLoad package.

 You need 2 MB ChipMem and the AGA chipset for AGA & CD32 versions, and
 0.5 MB Chipmem for the ECS version.
 
 You can quit the game by pressing F10 (key can be changed with	Tooltype 
 "QuitKey=").
 
 If you have problems with this installation please try first to get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad's WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, NOVBRMOVE, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also doesn't succeeds inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad's WWW-Page.

 For full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
	http://www.whdload.de/
 or	aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and	aminet:game/patch/

 version 2.4 (15.04.2020):
 - ECS: oops quitkey crashes on 68000 (issue #0004494)
 
 Version 2.3 (14.04.2020) done by JOTD:
 - ECS version: Exit key fixed to work on 68000 (issue #0004465)
 - ECS version: CD32 joypad support to pause game.
 - ECS version: "up" wasn't disabled when second button was used to jump
 
 Version 2.2 (08.04.2020) done by JOTD:
 - support for ECS version with same features (trainer, 2nd button jump...) (issue #0003886)
 - reduced audio dma delay (audio still okay) which fixes main sprite glitch
   on some fast machines (issue #0001181)
 
 Version 2.1 (04.04.2020) done by JOTD:
 - option to jump with blue/second button (issue #0004276)
 - added trainer: "easy mode": instant kill of enemies instead of hitting them 3 times
   which makes the game tedious (specially because of constant respawn). This was asked
   by someone recently, and I found that interesting (and easy to implement too)
 - added trainer: as soon as an Oscar is picked up, the exit is open (find the clapperboard)
 - CD남 version pause reenabled (with play or 'P' key)
 
 Version 2.0 (10.11.2019) done by JOTD:
 - war level underwater wall could not be broken due to access fault
   fixes that were failing to do the correct thing in some
   special cases (see source code for details)
 - added trainer: infinite lives & energy
 - adapted to whdload v17  
 - source code included
 
 Version 1.9 (26.03.2002) Wepl, unreleased:
 - decruncher moved to fastmem

 Version 1.8 (24.02.2001) Wepl
